/ooc God slayers?<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 <br>
A subject which (briefly) came up the other night in guild chat was whether or not we (as a guild) should take part in raids in the Plane of Hate, domain of our lord and master; Innoruuk!<br>
<br>
Well, the fact that we wouldn't take any negative faction hits seemed to sway the winnower towards the idea. Since then, I've realised another very good reason why it might<br>
be foolhardy to utterly reject the option of spending time in Innoruuk's domain. The shadow knight's epic quest requires an item from the ashenbone drakes from the Plane of Hate!<br>
<br>
Of course, this could then open up the possibility of attending raids to the Plane of Hate but bowing out before Innoruuk is challenged. <br>
<br>
From a role-playing perspective, I would feel much easier with the first of these two concepts:-<br>
<br>
1) Innoruuk, our dark lord, requires us to hate without exception. That which we hate, we kill. Innoruuk himself is not exempt from this theological viewpoint. Indeed, it could be argued that it is expected of us, ultimately, to send our god to his (temporary) death! What better a way of expressing our devotion to him? Any other approach must surely involve compromise and a weakening of our resolve. I'm sure that our dark lord would look upon us far less favourably if we showed any kind of weakness.<br>
<br>
2) We join in on raids to Hate but always leave before the final confrontation with Innoruuk. This poses two immediate problems. Firstly, we're not going to be very popular if we insist on leaving before completion of the raid. Secondly, how (in a roleplaying sense) can you feel comfortable with *grouping* with low-life *heathens* who are intent on slaying our god!? If you take the stance that slaying our own god is sacrilege, you must be consistent and also reject fraternising with those who would do this very thing.<br>
<br>
I've said my piece.<br>
<br>
